## Summary

The macaroon bakery package can be used to create, manipulate and verify [macaroons](http://theory.stanford.edu/~ataly/Papers/macaroons.pdf) without having to worry about how they will be transported or stored. The package provides a set of convenient methods and abstractions that can be easily integrated into any application.

## Installation

```
npm install @canonical/macaroon-bakery
```

## Usage

```js
import { Bakery } from "./src/bakery";
const bakery = new Bakery();

const url = "http://example.com/";
const headers = { header: "42" };
const callback = () => 42;

// will set additional headers:
// "Bakery-Protocol-Version": "2"
// and any stored macaroon related to the website http://example.com/
bakery.get(url, headers, callback);
```

